---
title: Tunisian-Spiced Chicken Salad with Harissa Roasted Carrots, Almonds & Apricot Vinaigrette
description: There are two kinds of salads in this world: side salads and star salads. And this one is certainly the latter! A warming Tunisian spice blend makes chicken cutlets shine with hints of caraway, smoked paprika, turmeric, cayenne, and cinnamon. Underneath all that flavor, apricot-dressed greens co-star in a hearty salad base that sweetens the deal. Harissa-roasted carrots color the plate with a touch of heat, while pickled shallot and almonds add tang and texture for a super-satisfying, show-stopping dinner salad.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/tunisian-spiced-chicken-salad-6c16f075.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/tunisian-spiced-chicken-salad-622610da0f84f659832ce1f9-4ec983bb.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: African
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 550 kcal
  fat: 28 g
  saturated fat: 4 g
  carbohydrates: 39 g
  sugar: 22 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 590 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/tunisian-spiced-chicken-salad-622610da0f84f659832ce1f9
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel, trim, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. (Halve any larger carrots lengthwise first.) Peel, trim, and thinly slice @shallot{1}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, ¼ tsp @harissa powder{1%tablespoon}, a big pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Line your baking sheet with foil or parchment paper before adding carrots.

Roast on top rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> Give the carrots a taste after roasting and add a pinch more harissa powder if you like things spicy.

Transfer to a #plate{}; spread out in an even layer to cool.

While carrots roast, in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, whisk together @red wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, 2 TBSP water, @sugar{½%teaspoon}, and a pinch of salt until sugar and salt have mostly dissolved. Stir in shallot; microwave for ~{30%seconds}.

Set aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

In a second #small bowl{}, whisk together @apricot jam{1}, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, 1 TBSP shallot pickling liquid, and @olive oil{2%tablespoon} until smooth. Season with salt and pepper.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels. Season all over with @Tunisian spice blend{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> If chicken is on the thicker side, cover with a lid for the last few minutes of cooking.

Remove chicken from pan and set aside. Add @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 2 TBSP dressing, and ¼ cup water to pan. Cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Return chicken to pan and turn a few times to coat.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} and slice crosswise.

In a #large bowl{}, toss @spinach{5%ounce} with as much remaining dressing as you like. Add carrots and shallot (draining first); toss to combine.

Divide salad between bowls; top with chicken. Pour any remaining sauce from pan over chicken. Garnish with @sliced almonds{½%ounce} and serve.